109
00:06:14,691 --> 00:06:16,718
No, not that much.

110
00:06:16,718 --> 00:06:19,746
What? Why is this your wish if you don't even like cake?

111
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:23,475
I just wanted to eat cake on a day like this.

112
00:06:23,475 --> 00:06:25,460
I see.

113
00:06:26,670 --> 00:06:29,590
But is it okay if you go home this late?

114
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:32,334
Hey. You were the one who wanted to hang out.

115
00:06:32,334 --> 00:06:34,978
I called my grandma and said I'll be late today.

116
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:36,938
Your grandma?

117
00:06:38,031 --> 00:06:41,584
I live with my grandma. It's just the two of us.

118
00:06:41,584 --> 00:06:43,695
You heard before, right?

119
00:06:43,695 --> 00:06:46,539
Is it a secret?

120
00:06:46,539 --> 00:06:48,725
That you live with your grandma?

121
00:06:50,027 --> 00:06:53,079
No. It's not a secret.

122
00:06:54,490 --> 00:06:57,241
- Thanks for the cake. 
 - Sure.

123
00:07:08,261 --> 00:07:10,538
I have to go this way.

124
00:07:10,538 --> 00:07:11,757
- I'm going this way. 
 - Okay.

125
00:07:11,757 --> 00:07:14,383
I'll get going then. See you tomorrow at the library.

126
00:07:14,384 --> 00:07:15,819
- Okay. 
 - By the way,

127
00:07:15,819 --> 00:07:19,314
Min will study with us. Is that okay?

128
00:07:19,314 --> 00:07:22,050
- Ha Min? 
 - Yes. We usually study together.

129
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,310
Okay. I'll see you tomorrow.

130
00:07:24,311 --> 00:07:25,870
Okay.

131
00:07:27,940 --> 00:07:29,624
Thank you.

132
00:07:30,771 --> 00:07:32,880
What?!

133
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:36,264
